The paper discusses the use of convolution and attention in deep neural network architectures, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI). The paper's focus on the mathematical underpinnings of these operations suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) sub-category.
